{
  "stem": "18575.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 312.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We played volleyball, basketball, and we did mischievous things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, for instance, we found in a basement in one of our apartments capsules with chlorine in it-- glass capsules with [? chlore ?] We took handfuls-- stole it.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [? we ?] [? called ?] it-- handfuls, packet-fulls of it, ride on a bicycle, and throw it into stores, and they exploded.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They stunk up horribly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We also-- oh, we did crazy things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We took sulfur, which is yellow, and if you light it up, sulfur, it smells horrible.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We used to stick it in the keyholes in apartments, light it up, and run away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And these-- the keyholes in Europe are very large.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It used to stunk up the apartment-- stinks, the nice things like that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was-- I was arrested twice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Once for jumping trolleys, the Polish trolleys, the Warsaw trolleys, had steps on both sides of the trolley.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the-- so if the trolley went one direction, they would open the door on that direction.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then if reverse, they would close that door, open opposite.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would jump on the steps that were closed and ride with the trolley as kids and then jump off.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were many accidents.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Where you jump off, you may jump off onto a truck.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The police put women, policewomen, on the trolleys.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when I was jump one time, she put a handcuff on me and locked me into the trolley so I couldn't jump off and got me out and brought me to the police station.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, of course, I gave them the telephone number.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They called in, and my father got me, and he was not very happy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He almost--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say I was 10 [LAUGHS] or 11.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
